## Conclusion

WezTerm replaces tmux, a color scheme plugin, and a hyperlink plugin — all in a
single Lua file. The leader key keeps shortcuts memorable and conflict-free, and
the local override pattern lets you track one config across all your machines.

Start with the basics (font, theme, leader key) and layer in workspaces and
hyperlinks as your workflow demands. The full config is on
[GitHub](https://github.com/systemhalted/dotfiles).
